response.Q0:
The first few rounds I inspected more than I did in the ones that followed.

At one point I saw that the most impact was to be made with the last nodes, so I just inspected those until I either hit about 6 inspections and just chose the highest one, or I saw something above 60 and went for that.
response.Q1: Yes, after a few rounds I only inspected the last nodes in the chains.
response.Q2: In the first few rounds I improved I think, but after that my performance was pretty stable in my opinion (besides the one time that I accidentally went for a high cost node).

response.Q0: Not hard in particular, but it did have a learning curve to figure out that the nodes at the end were the highest paying ones.
response.Q1: I have not participated in Web of Cash before.
response.Q2: It was quite fun to do! I'm quite curious to see what was the actual intention is of this research.
